--------------
M2 internship offer: Knowledge extraction in a corpus of scientific
publications and ontological modeling of citation contexts
--------------
This internship is funded by Lab-STICC UMR CNRS 6285
--------------

Lab-STICC (http://www.lab-sticc.fr/ <http://www.lab-sticc.fr/>) is one =
of the larger CNRS UMRs
in terms of staff size. It employs more than 600 researchers
in several locations of Oceanic Brittany. Lab-STICC member publications
have an important impact in many scientific disciplines.

The goal of this internship is to model and qualify this impact
through the citations of publications of members of Lab-STICC in
scientific literature.

Using corpora like ACM Digital Library or IEEE Explore
or HAL/arXiv (also DBLP, Google Scholar, etc.) we will first detect
the publications of a given individual in bibliographical reference =
lists,
then we will explore the contents of papers citing the giving individual
and analyze, by using Natural Language Processing techniques in
English or French, the citation contexts. Finally we will use ad hoc
ontologies to index the results.

One important result will be the (explicit or implicit) assessment of
the citation by the author of the article.

We will apply various measures to a conceptual graph representation
of the ontology, in order to obtain a rich view of the impact of=20
research of Lab-STICC members, using different granularity levels:
it will be possible to form queries involving one or more persons,
terms, topics or domains, and to obtain concrete metrological results
on the corresponding research activities.

--------------
Internship description
---------------
The main tasks will be:
- Development of the citation context extraction tool.
- Linguistic analysis of the citation contexts:
  - morphosyntax,
  - named entities,
  - anaphora resolution,
  - alignment with specific domain-dependent ontologies,
  - population of the ad hoc ontology,
  - sentiment detection.
- Modeling of results in the form of contextual graphs with
the possibility of querying.
- Comparison of various graph metrics to characterize the
scientific impact of a publication, a person or a team of Lab-STICC.

---------------
Candidate's profile
---------------
- Current curriculum: Master 2 in Computational Linguistics, Linguistic=20=

Engineering, or similar.
- Good knowledge of Python (in particular, NLTK).
- Curiosity and capacity to explore new domains in linguistics and
computer science.

-----------------
Conditions
-----------------
Paid internship of a duration of six months

To apply, please contact:  yannis.haralambous@imt-atlantique.fr =
<mailto:yannis.haralambous@imt-atlantique.fr>

Needed documents: CV, statement of intention, marks.

Location: D=C3=A9partement Informatique, IMT Atlantique (formerly =
T=C3=A9l=C3=A9com Bretagne), Brest, France.

Advisors: Yannis Haralambous (IMT Atlantique & UMR CNRS 6285 Lab-STICC)
           Gilles Coppin (IMT ATlantique & UMR CNRS 6285 Lab-STICC)
           Emmanuel Boutillon (Universit=C3=A9 de Bretagne-Sud & UMR =
CNRS 6285 Lab-STICC)

Contract type: internship.=20

Start: February 1st or March 1st, 2017, depending on the availability of =
the candidate.

